latin america 
we talked about how we can expand even further our global 
partnership he said 
secondly bush nudged kaifu on the trade question letting him 
know what was expected if that partnership was to continue 
the president said he took the opportunity to be just as clear 
as any congressman would have liked me to be on what needs to 
happen 
mosbacher said the summits major result was that both our 
governments for the first time realize we both have things to 
do to close the gap weve admitted we have problems and are 
starting to work to bring them together 
bush is sending mosbacher later this month for trade talks in 
tokyo he also directed secretary of state james a baker iii to 
meet with the japanese foreign minister to develop a trialogue 
with europe on global foreign policy and economic decisions 
