<TEXT>
the free haircuts bike repairs and other 
services offered by thousands of people at roadside stands were 
part of an official communist campaign to revive the spirit of a 
selfless soldierhero dead nearly 30 years 
as declared by the chinese communist youth league last month 
sunday was national learn from lei feng day 
chinese were supposed to do good deeds in honor of the soldier 
killed in 1962 when he backed his army truck into a utility pole 
leis deeds are legendary in china where everyone knows the 
stories of how the young soldier washed and mended his comrades 
clothes gave his rations away and read the works of revolutionary 
leader mao tsetung wherever he went 
but skeptics question the official story because of the 
suspicious existence of photographs of lei doing good deeds that he 
supposedly performed in secret 
shortly after leis death mao made him famous with an 
inscription to learn from comrade lei feng for years every 
child was taught to follow the lei feng spirit of being a 
rustless screw in the socialist machine 
in the recent years of reform and opening to the outside world 
the lei feng spirit was considered oldfashioned 
since last years massive prodemocracy movement however the 
chinese leadership has sought to summon back the old spirit of 
selfless sacrifice for the nation and has dusted lei off and put 
him back on a pedestal 
but few of those fixing bicycles and watches mending clothes 
handing out fliers on prevention of infectious diseases taking 
