that democracy will stick in nicaragua but a spokesman said policy 
toward asylum will clearly be reviewed 
nat kingsley of the state departments human rights bureau 
emphasized that under us law each application is treated 
individually whether it comes from england or albania 
obviously the conditions within a country play a role but it 
is the individuals relations in that country that are the deciding 
factor he said teams of state department analysts are 
constantly revising evaluations of many factors in each country 
including its human rights record 
for nicaragua its pretty early to tell how it will affect 
