<TEXT>
a minor earthquake measuring 39 on the richter 
scale shook eastern idaho but caused no damage a spokeswoman for 
the us geological survey said early today 
the temblor at 1151 pm mst sunday was felt by residents of 
the jackson wyo area near the idaho line according to pat 
jorgenson spokeswoman for the usgs in menlo park calif 
the epicenter of the quake was about 30 miles southwest of 
jackson jorgenson said the last recorded quake in eastern idaho 
was in the early 1980s she added 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale is considered capable 
of causing slight damage in the local area a quake of 4 can cause 
moderate damage 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 65 
