national congress the main south african black antigovernment 
group and its allied mass democratic movement 
he said the coup was aimed at ending widespread violence 
detentions of citizens corruption and deteriorating education and 
health services human rights monitoring groups say at least 700 
people have been detained in the homeland this year and about 200 
were still in detention sunday 
