<TEXT>
two house fires in alabama killed six 
people early today including three children whose father suffered 
burns while trying to reach them in their burning albertville home 
the others were a woman and two men who died of asphyxiation 
after fire broke out in their home at dothan 
authorities in albertville about 60 miles northeast of 
birmingham identified the victims as brandy leigh michael 12 
terry lynn michael 8 and jeremy daniel michael 4 
albertville fire marshal guy campbell said the father larry 
daniel michael 31 escaped through a window and was burned when he 
went back into the home trying to save the children he was taken 
to university hospital in birmingham for treatment of second and 
thirddegree burns 
campbell said the cause of the blaze which was reported at 152 
am was not immediately determined 
the fire in dothan which occurred at about 3 am was blamed 
on either cigarette smoking or an electric heater the three 
victims were identified as mildred b cook 70 johnny lee ward 
68 and wards son irvin price 51 
dothan is in southeast alabama 105 miles from montgomery 
