the soviet legislature monday directed two feuding 
caucasus republics to start negotiations toward settling the ethnic 
conflict that has killed hundreds of people in two years of unrest 
the supreme soviet returned to the emotional theme that has 
added a constant undercurrent of tension to its deliberations on a 
day during which a lack of a quorum frustrated efforts to take up a 
law on property ownership one of the key aspects of mikhail s 
gorbachevs economic reforms 
if approved the law on property would break soviet socialist 
tenets by allowing private individuals to own means of production 
and hire workers a final draft presented monday also dropped a 
preamble that declared socialist property the foundation of the 
socialeconomic system of the soviet union 
instead of using the longhated term of private property 
the measure instead calls it the property of citizens 
legislators approved a directive written on the dispute between 
armenia and azerbaijan by its presidium or executive body on a 
vote of 29820 with 45 abstentions after a debate punctuated by 
pleas for reason and angry shouting by armenian deputies 
supporters and opponents of the directive agreed it would not 
solve the key problems of the region but they differed on whether 
it was a step forward 
every passionate speech is one more letter in a death sentence 
for a living person said deputy nikolai medvedev of lithuania 
speaking in support of the directive 
armenian deputy lyudmilla arytyunyan told reporters all 14 
armenians present voted against it 
armenians say azerbaijan has lost the moral right to rule the 
disputed nagornokarabakh territory and demand that it be taken 
from azerbaijan and placed under national jurisdiction she said 
control of predominantly armenian nagornokarabakh is at the 
center of the dispute between the two republics but the directive 
said nothing about nagornokarabakh 
asked about medvedevs plea she said i would like to ask 
is it better to live on your knees or die standing up 
it gave the interior ministry which controls the police the 
kgb and the two governments two months to report back on who was 
responsible for ethnic attacks on armenians in baku azerbaijan in 
midjanuary that killed scores of people and led the kremlin to 
send in soldiers 
an angry vice president anatoly i lukyanov who presided over 
the session told legislators it was a shame to show on the 
daily delayed tv broadcast that they could not muster a quorum to 
debate the property law 
some of the missing lawmakers were occupied by sundays election 
to local and republic governing councils in russia the ukraine and 
byelorussia he said 
twothirds of the 542 members of both houses of the supreme 
soviet or 361 members must be present to pass legislation on 
monday morning 346 were present and that swelled to 364 when 
lukyanov brought the 34article bill up for an itembyitem vote 
but then only 352 deputies voted on the first item and lukyanov 
gave up further consideration of the bill until tuesday 
it was brought to the supreme soviet two weeks ago just after 
the communist party declared that individuals should be allowed to 
own factories and other means of production legislators found it 
too vague and sent it back for more committee work 
the new draft strengthens provisions allowing individuals to 
hire others long prohibited by soviet socialism as exploitation 
as long as they are provided adequate wages and benefits 
yuri kalmykov chairman of the supreme soviet committee on 
legislation told legislators the committees rejected a specific 
mention of private property in the law because soviets cannot agree 
on what it means 
