parents and when mom and dad die suddenly theyre really alone 
gahm said about 700 singles from around the country belong to 
the organization which she founded four years ago they meet 
regularly to share stories about their common bond 
many live and work on farms especially in the midwest others 
who now live in town trace their roots to agriculture 
they gathered here in the heart of the cornbelt from thursday 
through sunday for the organizations fourth national convention 
