parliament on monday adopted a law 
restoring names the 15 million ethnic turks and other native 
bulgarian moslems had to forsake under a forced assimilation 
campaign launched by the old communist leadership 
under the new law all bulgarian citizens can choose their own 
names without restriction 
some ethnic turks are still unhappy with the law which includes 
a clause that requires name changes to be approved by a court 
about 3000 moslems held a protest vigil outside the 
cordonedoff parliament building monday saying they would not 
leave until they saw the law in writing they were informed of the 
laws passage by medyud doganov a turkish leader and two 
legislators 
also monday 30000 miners and other workers were on strike in 
