alleging the government has not kept its promise to increase their 
pay and improve working conditions 
ethnic turks and other moslems were forced to take bulgarian 
names in an oftenviolent assimilation campaign authored by 
communist leader todor zhivkov who was deposed in november 
most of bulgarias 9 million people belong to the bulgarian 
orthodox church 
the name law became the centerpiece of the parliamentary session 
after other reform items were shelved partly because they had not 
been discussed with the opposition talks between the communist 
government and opposition were suspended three weeks ago over 
disagreement over political and economic reform 
communists in bulgaria unlike those in other soviet bloc 
countries have retained much of their clout in national politics 
