gonzalez estimated those measures along with suspension of 
federal subsidies and deferral of payments to state contractors 
would save 2 billion a year 
he did not say how many public employees would be laid off or 
retired but newspapers speculated tens of thousands might have to 
go about onefourth of argentinas 125 million workers are 
employed by the government 
the general labor confederation with 3 million members 
argentinas largest labor organization said it was studying the 
government measures it has criticized earlier versions and has not 
ruled out a general strike 
restructuring of the national banks is aimed at reducing losses 
that contribute to a deficit this year of about 70 billion or 
1215 percent of gross national product 
because of poor lending and collection practices the mortgage 
bank has run up a deficit of 1 billion with the central bank 
until now the central bank simply printed money to cover such 
losses 
a report last month in the newspaper pagina 12 citing bank 
data said the national development bank was owed 19 billion by 
its 60 largest debtors including the state telephone electric 
coal railroad and gas companies 
closing the mortgage bank and laying off public employees are 
seen as a test of the governments resolve to address the deficit 
without printing money 
in past months the government has announced plans to retire or 
transfer hundreds of employees of the state railroad mortgage bank 
and congress it backed off in each case because of union 
opposition 
