the most common reasons for visiting schools included attending 
a scheduled parentteacher conference which 71 percent had 
attended or class or school program which 64 percent had attended 
the survey commissioned by newsweek magazine for the national 
pta and chryslers dodge division was based on a national sample 
of parents in 538 households with children enrolled in kindergarten 
through 12th grade ninety percent of the children are in public 
school with 10 percent in either private or parochial schools 
