john p zanotti president and publisher of the 
cincinnati enquirer was named publisher of the arizona republic 
and the phoenix gazette on monday 
zanotti 41 fills a vacancy created by the retirement of pat 
murphy on aug 8 unlike murphy he will be in charge of the 
newspapers business as well as their editorial side a spokesman 
for the papers said 
in addition to his role as publisher of the newspapers zanotti 
will be executive vice president and chief executive officer of the 
arizona business gazette and of phoenix newspapers inc which 
publishes the three papers said the spokesman william shover 
the appointment culminates a sevenmonth search throughout the 
united states said frank russell president of indianapolisbased 
central newspapers inc which owns phoenix newspapers inc 
john zanotti is a person with a proven track record as 
publisher of a major metropolitan newspaper and he is uniquely 
qualified to lead these newspapers into the 1990s russell said 
in a news release 
zanotti was named president and publisher of the enquirer in 
1985 a year after joining gannett co inc the owner of the paper 
he also has had operational responsibilities without editorial 
duties for the cincinnati post under a joint operating agreement 
with the enquirer 
as publisher of the republic and gazette zanotti will be in 
charge of news and business operations returning the newspapers to 
the situation that existed when darrow tully was publisher shover 
said 
murphy who replaced tully was in charge of news operations 
only while william hogan vice president and general manager for 
pni was in charge of the business side 
hogan is staying on shover said adding that it is uncertain 
what his new duties will entail 
zanotti takes over as publisher immediately shover said 
the republic and gazette had a combined weekday circulation of 
about 418000 and a sunday circulation of about 507000 according 
to september 1988 figures certified by the audit bureau of 
circulation 
the enquirer had a weekday morning circulation of about 193000 
and a sunday circulation of about 327124 according to abc figures 
zanotti majored in spanish at the university of southern 
california and earned a law degree at arizona state university in 
1974 according to a company biography 
after four years practicing law with the los angeles firm of 
omelveny and myers he joined hartehanks communications inc as 
general counsel later becoming vice president and in 1983 
president of hartehanks direct marketings central group 
