cabinet ministers from prime minister yitzhak 
shamirs rightwing likud bloc on monday gave conditional approval 
to usmediated peace talks with palestinians 
but new complications arose when leaders in the occupied lands 
said palestinians in the territories will serve on a delegation to 
talks with israel only if the plo chooses it 
the likud ministers decision came at the end of a fivehour 
meeting in shamirs office and was adopted unanimously 
israel is interested to continue the peace process according 
to its peace initiative and to hold the proposed meeting with a 
palestinian group in order to work out the methods of elections in 
judea samaria and gaza it said using biblical names for the 
occupied west bank 
however the decision released by shamirs office set several 
conditions 
it said israel should speak in one voice and therefore an 
agreement with labor was needed in essential and basic 
issues guaranteeing israeli sovereignty over the whole jerusalem 
and preventing the plo from taking over the process 
the israeli peace initiative approved by the government last 
may offers palestinian elections in the occupied lands to choose 
negotiators for talks on limited autonomy the final disposition of 
the occupied territories is to be decided later 
israel refuses to negotiate the status of jerusalem which it 
has declared its capital after annexing the citys eastern arab 
part it was captured from jordan in the 1967 middle east war 
the palestinians who have been waging a nearly 27monthold 
revolt against israeli rule in the west bank and occupied gaza 
strip demand an independent state with east jerusalem as its 
capital 
secretary of state james a baker iii trying to bridge various 
differences has suggested several compromise moves to bring about 
preliminary israelipalestinian talks in cairo egypt 
baker has reportedly suggested israel accept any negotiator 
registered as a resident of the west bank or gaza strip that may 
include palestinian exiles somehow affiliated with the plo and 
arabs who actually live in east jerusalem and thus satisfy plo 
demands 
the likud decision made no reference to the question of 
palestinians deported from the occupied lands suggesting likud may 
be ready to accept them as negotiators 
but the ministers ruled out participation of east jerusalem 
arabs saying they shall not participate in the process linked to 
the peace initiative either by participating in elections or by 
being elected 
a positive response from likud is seen as crucial in the israeli 
acceptance of the us proposals the main elements have already 
been accepted by the leftleaning labor party likuds political 
rival and partner in the coalition government 
labor has threatened to leave the coalition if likud blocks the 
peace process 
likuds conditional approval remained vague regarding the agenda 
of cairo talks which israel wants to be limited to its elections 
plan the palestinians want an open agenda enabling them to raise 
independence demands 
another part of the likud decision touched on the participation 
of the plo which the palestinians call their sole legitimate 
representative israel considers the palestine liberation 
organization a terrorist group and refuses to negotiate with it 
attempts by plo to penetrate or take control over the process 
in any form would lead to a stoppage of the meeting and israels 
withdrawal from it the statement said 
the likud decision was announced hours after 34 palestinian 
leaders from the occupied territories signed a statement demanding 
the plo select any delegation to peace talks with israel 
no palestinian from the israelioccupied territories will 
participate in any delegation that is not formed or announced by 
the plo it said 
bakers compromises reportedly included having egypt announce 
the palestinian delegation and the palestinian statement saying it 
should be made public by the plo was likely to further complicate 
peace moves 
another complication is the new us position of citing jewish 
neighborhoods in east jerusalem as settlements a definition 
earlier reserved for settlements in the west bank and gaza strip 
it certainly did not help a senior likud official noted 
after the meeting 
the us statements regarding jerusalem on monday drew angry 
responses from israeli leaders including labor head and vice 
premier shimon peres who stressed his partys commitment to united 
jerusalem as israels capital 
shamirs spokesman yossi ahimeir predicted labor would accept 
likuds demands 
these are very easy in my mind for labor being committed to 
united jerusalem and the idea that the plo would not penetrate 
the process we dont foresee any special problems with labor 
ahimeir said 
