the ratings still begin with a decimal point but 
cable news network is standing by its fledgling dinnertime 
newscast the world today 
cnn launched the onehour program in october starting it at 6 
pm est a time slot in which its second halfhour competes 
directly with the nightly newscasts of abc cbs and nbc in the 
eastern and central time zones where 75 percent of the nations 
viewers live 
cnns new show gained some immediate attention with the 
selection of catherine crier up until last year a texas judge to 
join veteran newsman bernard shaw at the anchor desk crier in 
atlanta shaw in washington 
the ratings show they arent yet in the same league with abcs 
peter jennings nbcs tom brokaw and cbs dan rather far from it 
last weeks nielsens showed abcs world news tonight winning 
its eighth consecutive victory with an 113 ratings average 
followed by the nbc nightly news with a 101 average and the 
cbs evening news with a 99 
cnn says its ratings are averaging a 7 but the gap is even 
bigger than it looks in broadcasting one rating point equals 
921000 homes in cable one point for cnn equals 547820 homes 
the number cnn estimates it serves 
but cnn says ratings for the world today are growing every 
month and already are 16 percent better than the two programs 
previously in the same time period 
