35 a civil judge for five years said the parallels are 
tremendous between her old profession and her new one 
as a trial lawyer she said she gathered facts by interviewing 
witnesses and then delivered those facts clearly to a judge or 
jury as a judge she said she had to glean facts from piles of 
evidence and draw objective conclusions 
