<TEXT>
christ the redeemer the famous 
statue that watches over rio is being repaired after more than a 
halfcentury of battering by rain mountain winds and dramatic 
temperature changes 
adverse weather conditions have done a great deal of damage 
said architect joel ghivelder the renovation is absolutely 
necessary and timely 
ghivelder is coordinating the 2 million renovation for the 
globo media empire which is splitting the cost with the brazilian 
subsidiary of the royal dutch shell oil company 
seeping moisture has reached iron plates beneath the 125foot 
statues light green soapstone facade causing them to rust and 
expand to up to eight times their original size ghivelder said 
the expansion has caused cracks and swelling on the statues 
surface and some chunks of soapstone have already fallen off he 
said 
no one has been hurt by the falling stones one of which weighed 
25 pounds and ghivelder attributes that to christs presence 
engineers will preserve as much of the statues original surface 
material as possible but about 10 percent of the soapstone must be 
replaced the architect said 
scaffolding will cover the christ until about july and the 
restoration to include landscaping and improvements in public 
facilities will be completed in the fall the hope is to finish 
the work by the statues 59th anniversary in october 
until then the final flights of stairs leading to the monument 
will be sealed off 
the renovation is extremely important and urgent said jose 
geraldo machado technical director of riotur the municipal 
tourism board brazils image is established through rio and the 
christ statue along with sugar loaf mountain and copacabanas 
beaches are the citys three top symbols 
heitor de costa silva conceived the statue in the early 1920s in 
a competition sponsored by a popular magazine to choose a 
national monument 
french sculptur paul landowski created the christs 12foot 
high 35ton head the hands weigh nine tons each and are 75 feet 
across 
when french engineers had designed the outstreched arms and 
body the parts were sent from paris dragged up 2400foot 
corcovado mountain and mounted on supporting pillars the statue 
was inaugurated oct 12 1931 
hundreds of thousands of people visit the site every year to 
see the statue and enjoy the spectacular view of guanabara bay the 
open atlantic the mountains hills and the vibrant city below 
in his book the insiders guide to rio christopher pickard 
wrote in truth the view is beyond description words and 
photographs are not enough 
ghivelder said christ the redeemer is one of the countrys 
biggest attractions for both foreigners and brazilians we want to 
recover the statue and give it back to the city clean neat and 
beautiful 
</TEXT>
