latinos are younger on average than the rest of the 
population in 1980 their median age was 23 compared to 30 for 
americans in general 
that means more are in the childbearing years and they are 
producing a higher growth rate than the rest of the nation in 
1988 hispanics averaged 94 births per 1000 women ages 18 to 44 
compared to 67 per 1000 for the rest of the country 
