<TEXT>
southeast asias answers to the champs elysees 
and fifth avenue are orchard road in singapore and nathan road in 
hong kong both beacons to tourists and fashionconscious shoppers 
in the exotic orient here are two stories describing what has 
become some of the most expensive real estate in the world 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
orchard road is the very symbol of singapore 
one of the worlds smallest and most successful countries a place 
where consumerism is indeed conspicuous 
the official guide to this citystate says orchard road is a 
testament to modern singapore with its pedestrian malls shaded by 
huge trees and enlivened by small gardens full of tropical blooms 
and lush greenery 
this 2395squaremile country with no natural resources except 
a strategic location and the skills of its 26 million people 
enjoys the highest standard of living in southeast asia and the 
secondbest in all asia after japan 
with hong kong it is arguably the most unabashed materialistic 
society in the region 
orchard road recently was rated in a private survey by the new 
york real estate firm huberth amp peters inc as the worlds 
10thpriciest street in terms of commercial space for rent 
conspicuous consumers abound both the domestic and tourist 
variety 
statusconscious chuppies as chinese yuppies are known 
sport rolex watches designer clothes jade rings mercedesbenz 
cars and a taste for the latest in food and fashion 
orchard road is where they can shop till they drop eat till 
they pop and then plop into the swimming pool at the hilton 
dynasty mandarin or some other elegant hotel 
named for the nutmeg and tropical fruit plantations that lined 
it in colonial days orchard road is centrally located and easily 
reached by singapores 2yearold subway system thousands of 
domestic servants most of them from the philippines throng the 
treelined street on sundays the usual day off for maids here 
they catch up on gossip from home and take advantage of the 
three main features of orchard road shopping eating and 
peoplewatching 
the survey by the new york real estate firm showed that one 
square foot of shop space along the 1mile thoroughfare costs an 
average of 175 a year by comparison the survey found that one 
square foot for a year costs 675 on the ginza in tokyo the 
worlds costliest shopping district 
a check by the associated press found that the more desirable 
retail space on orchard road fetched more than 350 each year rent 
for shops in the popular but by no means topoftheline lucky 
plaza is now 368 per square foot a year almost double that of 
last year 
the multistory lucky plaza houses scores of shops selling 
electrical appliances clothing jewelry watches cameras 
cosmetics shoes sporting goods luggage radios and hifi 
equipment plus restaurants and bookstores 
while the mostly locally owned retail outlets in orchard road 
pay the highest rents in singapore they also charge from 30 
percent to 50 percent more for their merchandise than other 
shopping areas much of it consists of highpriced imports and for 
everyday necessities most singaporeans eschew the glittering 
boulevard for more modest stores in chinatown and elsewhere 
the huberth amp peters survey found one common denominator to the 
most expensive streets around the world was that they almost always 
contain designer names and upscale shops 
the brands prominently displayed along orchard road include 
cartier gucci christian dior dunhill omega rolex boutiques 
and department stores offer the latest in high style and casual 
wear from the fashion centers of europe and north america 
not all the fancy branded goods are what they seem however 
many tourists are pestered by touts to buy genuine copywatches 
from certain stores at a fraction of the price of the real thing 
the selling of fakes is at the heart of the touting problem 
touts are there mainly to persuade people to buy fakes says 
police deputy superintendent ng kee hoe 
in the eight months prior to feb 1 the police arrested 126 
touts and seized 11564 fake watches from 61 shops first offenders 
can be fined up to 5000 or jailed up to six months or both 
some touts appear to have their own turf and competition among 
them is as fierce as that between mcdonalds and burger king 
one of the first mcdonalds outlets in singapore was in liat 
towers at 541 orchard road it proved so popular that after the 
burger king franchise holder bought the building big mac lost the 
coveted location to the whopper 
