<TEXT>
medicares catastrophic healthcare program is 
history but its legacy lingers in this years tax forms 
congress didnt kill the yearold medical program until after 
the internal revenue service had sent the 1989 tax returns to the 
printer so forms 1040 and 1040a contain instructions for payment 
of a seniorsonly catastrophic surtax that doesnt exist 
the catastrophic question is a oneyear quirk in the income tax 
picture that bodes well for senior citizens but several other 
continuing provisions in federal law also help to make tax time a 
little less taxing for the elderly 
these provisions which include a higher standard deduction and 
more liberal filing requirements for the elderly mean many people 
must reacquaint themselves with the tax code when they turn 65 
even if theyve been doing their own taxes for decades 
many older taxpayers are unfamiliar with the special 
provisions of the internal revenue code which become available to 
them when they reach age 65 the house aging committee said in 
its annual tax guide for older americans 
in addition to benefits that automatically become available at 
age 65 other changes in the taxfiling routine occur as older 
americans mrity benefits and rules for pension and annuity income 
the irs also offers free taxpreparation help to the elderly 
through two programs volunteer income tax assistance and tax 
counseling for the elderly people can call the taxpayer service 
number listed in their tax package or in the telephone book to find 
out where to get assistance 
volunteers in both programs can help people prepare simple tax 
forms although the latter is specifically targeted toward the 
needs of the elderly tax counseling for the elderly is jointly 
sponsored by the irs and the american association of retired 
persons which provides 30000 trained counselors to assist more 
than 15 million older taxpayers a year with federal and state tax 
forms 
the program also serves more than 47000 shutins who cannot 
visit tax assistance sites 
we find a lot of people who are intimidated by the form 
itself said aarps patty hoath we also find people who 
perhaps have not been in a situation to do the tax form in the 
past such as someone who is newly widowed 
others need help dealing with tax issues they havent faced in 
the past such as taxation of social security benefits or 
interpretation of pension benefit statements ms hoath said 
the irs has notified senior citizens that because the 
catastrophic surtax was repealed they should ignore line 54 on 
form 1040 and line 23 on form 1040a anyone who made extra 
estimated tax payments during 1989 to cover the catastrophic surtax 
will receive a refund of their overpayments 
we have tried to get the word out that even though the line 
appears on the tax form the provision no longer exists said irs 
spokesman steve pyrek some people no matter what will include 
information on that line of the return 
the repeal of the supplemental medicare premium affects about 40 
percent of the elderly who would have paid 2250 for every 150 
of federal income tax liability about 6 percent would have paid 
the maximum amount of 800 per person 
congress repealed the catastrophic program in november under 
pressure from higherincome senior citizens many of whom already 
had duplicate private coverage and who said the expanded government 
medical benefits werent worth the price tag 
</TEXT>
