<TEXT>
as the american population ages amid a 
mini baby boom an increasing number of parents must care for 
grandmother as well as bring up baby and juggle fulltime jobs 
to help families caught in that triple bind stride rite corp 
has opened what company officials say is the nations only 
intergenerational day care center 
karen leibold director of the center at the companys 
headquarters hopes it will become the kind of place where working 
parents can drop off their children and elderly relatives in the 
morning and know they will have been fed entertained educated and 
cared for when they pick them up in the evening 
the fourth floor of the shoemanufacturing company has been 
remodeled to accommodate up to 55 children and 24 older people the 
program is open both to the 500 stride rite employees in cambridge 
and community residents 
the weekly fee for elderly care is 140 child care fees range 
from 130 to 170 a week 
on a recent visit to the center 4yearolds were being dressed 
for a winter walk toddlers were puzzling over a talking toy and a 
group of very excited youngsters was getting a cooking lesson 
were making play dough one cried out 
at the other end of the floor in a sunny room affectionately 
dubbed the library a grandmother was relaxing on a couch and 
talking with a staff member its nice in here she said 
glancing around the room that will eventually have additional 
ottomans and livingroom lamps its comfortable 
stride rite was already a corporate pioneer in providing day 
care for its employees when a newspaper article on the dilemma of 
families caught between caring for elderly relatives and children 
caught the attention of chairman arnold hyatt about three years ago 
he immediately wrote a memo to the director of the companys day 
care program saying the company should create a program for the old 
as well as the young 
a survey of stride rite employees found about 25 percent were 
caring for an elderly relative and an additional 13 percent 
expected to do so in the future leibold said these figures 
mirrored national trends 
she said the study also indicated that a daughter track 
existed as well as the mommy track mommy track refers to the 
course many females take when they juggle jobs and child care 
leibold said national council on aging studies found that most care 
givers for the elderly are women who then may be forced to limit 
the time devoted to a career 
the result of the survey and hyatts memo was a 700000 
investment by stride rite in designing 8500 square feet of space 
into groups of rooms for children and the elderly with 
administrative offices and dining facilities in between 
painted in purple teal and apricot the center is designed to 
create a feeling of comfort and cheer to look like grandmothers 
front porch rather than an institution or even a corporate 
office stride rite spokeswoman deborah singer said 
at one end of the floor is an area set aside for the elderly it 
includes an arts and crafts area and the library designed to 
look like someones living room leibold said 
the other end of the floor has classrooms for ages 2 through 5 
all furnished with miniature furniture splotchy watercolors and a 
scattering of dolls and wooden blocks 
the dining area shared by both groups has adultsize tables 
and chairs and childsize tables and chairs a long counter 
featuring a sink a hot pad and adjustable chairs will provide 
facilities for the adults to cook and the children to learn to cook 
what weve done is encourage interaction between children and 
the elderly and ensure the privacy of each group leibold said 
from 730 am to 530 pm both groups have supervised 
activities meals crafts and exercise programs sometimes 
together leibold hopes this will help to get rid of stereotypes 
that old people and young people have about each other 
the program is designed for elderly who do not need extensive 
medical attention but require general supervision for daily 
activities only two are currently at the center and leibold said 
the company is working to inform employees and the community of the 
elderly program 
stride rite was one of the first companies to open its own day 
care center in 1971 and leibold hopes the intergenerational 
center will be a model for other such centers 
singer said the facility hopes to provide its elderly with 
meaningful activities a computer will be installed and singer 
hopes that one day the seniors could produce a newsletter for the 
center the company is working with wheelock college and the 
somervillecambridge elder services organization to develop elderly 
programs 
families are very stressed today leibold said fewer and 
fewer families are living within close contact with each other 
the new center will help bring the generations together she 
said 
</TEXT>
