lawrence armour said that brings the total amount american express 
has invested in shearson in recent months to well over 1 billion 
shearson expanded rapidly through acquisitions in the 1980s to 
become the nations secondlargest brokerage but its recent 
struggles to cope with a downturn in the securities business have 
led to thousands of layoffs and turmoil in its management ranks 
american expreses first moved to strengthen its grip last month 
by ousting chairman and chief executive peter a cohen the man who 
guided the firms explosive growth and replacing him with howard 
l clark jr american express chief financial officer 
as a result of a review led by clark we are confident that 
