cogen technologies inc said today it has secured 
870 million in financing to build a cogeneration power plant in 
linden nj to provide power to lindenarea chemical and refining 
companies and to consolidated edison co of new york 
the financing from general electric power funding corp is one 
of the largest packages ever for a cogeneration plant in the united 
states robert c mcnair president of houstonbased cogen said 
cogen and its affiliates will own and operate the plant which 
is designed to provide 614 megawatts of electric capacity and up to 
1 million pounds per hour of steam the company said the 
electricity also could supply up to 860000 homes 
construction is expected to begin in october with startup in 
mid 1992 
the plant will be powered by natural gas provided by public 
service and gas co and elizabethtown gas both of new jersey 
cogen said the plant would be one of the cleanest facilities of 
its size in the nation with exhaust emissions levels only a 
fraction of those produced by coal or oilfired utility power 
plants 
