said celeste georkakis an analyst with cargill investor services 
inc in new york 
the rally was considered especially significant though because 
coffee futures surpassed 1 a pound a price at which coffee had 
not traded since early july when the international coffee 
organization lifted export quotas and exposed prices to the free 
market 
coffee futures plunged below 70 cents a pound last year as 
producers sold out their warehoused stocks but the recent rise 
indicates the market is moving toward a more balanced 
supplyanddemand situation 
with prices now above 1 chances for a return to export quotas 
look slim said sandra kaul an analyst with shearson lehman hutton 
inc who said that at these prices producers are likely to become 
more willing sellers 
the concern about nearby availability is likely to moderate up 
here at higher price levels which should allow sales to pick up 
she said 
copper futures rose sharply on new yorks commodity exchange on 
supply worries exacerbated by the comexs report that its warehouse 
stocks of copper fell 175 short tons friday and by the london metal 
exchanges report of a 4475 metric ton decline last week in its 
stocks 
