<TEXT>
general motors corp said it would consolidate 
its two engine development operations into one organization 
the move which combines engine research and development 
operations at gms buickoldsmobilecadillac and 
chevroletpontiacgm of canada groups is designed to help 
streamline the nations largest automaker 
this action which will improve our ability to bring great 
products more quickly to the marketplace will greatly benefit our 
car and truck division customers gm president robert stempel 
said monday 
in 1984 gm underwent a reorganization that combined five engine 
operations into two beginning in 1987 gm embarked on its action 
plan a costcutting effort aimed at cutting up to 13 billion 
in costs by the end of this year 
the effective dates of the latest engine consolidation will be 
determined later 
spokesman charles licari said the recommendations were not made 
with the goal of idling facilities or laying off workers 
on the other hand we know there are efficiencies to be gained 
by integrating the cpc and boc power train operations licari 
said our goals will be to grow the business bring in contract 
work and design and manufacture vehicles that help sell vehicles 
he said 
general manager for the new division will be richard m 
donnelly product manager of the boc powertrain division 
</TEXT>
