<TEXT>
the national basketball association is 
crying foul at gte corp accusing the company of trademark 
infringement by launching a sweepstakes contest with a tiein to 
the nba championship series 
in a lawsuit filed last week in us district court the nba is 
asking for an injunction halting gtesylvanias step up to the 
line sweepstakes as well as unspecified monetary damages for 
alleged trademark infringement and unfair trade practices 
if the court orders the contest cancelled the suit asks that 
gte be required to notify all entrants by mail and to run 
corrective advertising 
the nba said the contest is substantially similar to a 
sweepstakes being conducted by fritolay inc which paid a 
substantial sum for the privilege to link its contest to the 
nba finals 
the gte sweepstakes is simply an attempt to take 
plaintiffs valuable property rights by improperly associating 
themselves with the good will and reputation of the nba the suit 
said 
a spokesman for stamfordbased gte said monday the company 
could not comment on the suit until its attorneys had a chance to 
study it 
fullpage advertisements for the gte sweepstakes appeared in 
inserts in newspapers and magazines nationwide on feb 18 
according to the suit the ads were constructed and designed to 
imply and suggest the sponsorship endorsement or approval of the 
nba 
ryan partnership a stamford marketing firm sought permission 
in november to use the nba trademarks for a gte sweepstakes but was 
denied the suit said a woman who answered the telephone at ryan 
said there was no one available to comment 
the nba said it sent a letter to gte and ryan on feb 26 
demanding they call a halt to the contest but that the defendants 
refused 
the gtesylvania sweepstakes ad invites entrants in the body of 
the promotion to win a trip to the championship finals and a 
share of 25000 in prizes 
in smaller print readers are advised that four grand prize 
winners will receive an expensepaid trip for a family of four to 
the first two games of the nba championship finals and that 
prizewinners will participate in a freethrow shootout with 
25000 in prizes 
in addition the official entry form states yes i would like 
to win a trip to the nba championship finals and a share of 25000 
in prizes 
the nba said gte has not been authorized to conduct any 
freethrow contest in connection with the championship series but 
that the ad falsely suggests otherwise 
entrants in the fritolay contest on the other hand are vying 
for the opportunity to win a trip to the nba playoffs and the 
chance to compete in a freethrow shooting contest during halftime 
of a conference playoff game or during game 4 of the finals the 
nba said 
